  }
}

function makeSound(animal: Animal) {
  console.log(animal.sound());
}

makeSound(new Duck()); // Output: Quack!
makeSound(new Cat()); // Output: Meow!
```
In this example, the `makeSound` function takes an `Animal` object as a parameter, but it doesn't care about the actual type of the object. As long as the object has a `sound()` method, it can be used as an `Animal` object.

